OL,6,FThe court heard how within six months
OL,7,Fof Blatchford's relationship he became
OL,8,Fincreasingly paranoid and controlling,
OL,9,Fas well as physically violent.
OL,11,FHis victim was prevented from speaking
OL,12,Fto her children and was often locked
OL,13,Fin the house. Her bank card was also
OL,14,Ftaken and Blatchford withdrew her
OL,15,Fmoney, leaving her in debt.
OL,17,FShe was required to keep her phone in
OL,18,FBlatchford's view and allow him to
OL,19,Fexamine her messages.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
