OL,6,FOn one occasion the victim stood up to
OL,7,FBlatchford so he took an overdose in
OL,8,Ffront of her, the court heard.
OL,10,FAfter the relationship ended in March
OL,11,F2024, the victim went to Blatchford's
OL,12,Fhouse to collect her belongings. When
OL,13,Fshe tried to leave, Blatchford began
OL,14,Fbeing threatening and abusive.
OL,16,FWhen the victim arrived back at her
OL,17,Fhome, Blatchford strangled her until
OL,18,Fthe point she struggled to breathe.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
